# Dependency-Safe Edits

The pptides app has **tight coupling**. Changing one file can break 20+ consumers.

## Before Editing Any File

1. **Read `DEPENDENCY_MAP.md`** — lists blast radius for peptides.ts, constants.ts, trial config, AuthContext, Coach, edge functions.
2. **Grep consumers:** `rg "from '@/path/to/file'" src/` — see who imports the file.
3. **TRIAL_DAYS:** If changing trial duration, update **all 8 locations** (src/config/trial.ts, vite.config, index.html, create-checkout, stripe-webhook, trial-reminder, send-welcome-email, admin-actions).
4. **peptides.ts / constants.ts:** 20–25+ consumers. Changes to exports or derived values (FREE_PEPTIDE_IDS, PEPTIDE_COUNT) affect many pages.
5. **Edge functions:** Request/response shape must match frontend. Redeploy after changes.

## After Every Change

- Run `npm run predeploy` (type-check + build) before commit.
- Fix type-check and build errors before pushing.

## High-Risk Files

| File | Approx consumers |
|------|------------------|
| src/data/peptides.ts | 20+ |
| src/lib/constants.ts | 25+ |
| src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx | 15+ |
| src/config/trial.ts | 8 (frontend + 5 edge functions) |
